DataElement.preferredName: Pathology Report Review Parameter Reviewer Role PathologyReportReviewParameterReviewerRole
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A report that provides a description of the gross and microscopic examination of the specimen and is used to make a diagnosis and to determine treatment. It defines which structures and organs of the body are involved by the tumor, verifies the primary site of the cancer and describes the extent to which it has spread.:The act of appraisal, evaluation, or analysis.:Any factor that defines a system and determines (or limits) its performance._A person with a responsibility for examining something to make sure that it is adequate, accurate, or correct.:The usual or expected function of something; the part something plays in an action or event._Event associated with the review of a surgical pathology report
